decimales.tooltip: In those generations that return a number with a decimal part, the number of decimal places to display in the return is indicated.

limpiarfiltros.label: Clear filters
limpiarfiltros.tooltip: Clear applied filters reverting to original data

apikey.label: API-Key
apikey.tooltip: Enter the API key for communication with the REST service

pasaportesindc.label: Passport without DC
pasaportesindc.tooltip: Passport number without the control digit.

tipotarjeta.label: Select card type
tipotarjeta.placeholder: Select a specific type to generate only this type.

cantidad.label: Quantity (char./word/para.)
cantidad.placeholder: Number of characters, words or paragraphs to generate
cantidad.tooltip: If the type is 'Characters', it will be the number of characters to generate, if the type is 'Words', it will be the number of words to generate, and if it is 'Paragraphs', it will be the number of paragraphs to generate

gaussianomedia.label: Mean
gaussianomedia.tooltip: Mean (μ) is the expected average value of the distribution. It represents the central point around which the values generated by the distribution cluster. More formally, it is the location parameter of the normal distribution, calculated as the sum of all values divided by the number of values.

gaussianodeviado.label: Standard deviation
gaussianodeviado.tooltip: Standard deviation (σ) is a measure of the dispersion or variability of the values around the mean (μ) of the distribution. It indicates how much the generated values deviate from the mean, with a higher standard deviation indicating greater data dispersion, and a lower standard deviation indicating values are more clustered around the mean.

calculadoralogx.tooltip: Logarithm to base X (specified in the second operator)

areaa.label: Value A
areaa.tooltip: Each shape implies a value: 'square': Side length, 'rectangle': Width, 'triangle': Base, 'parallelogram': Base, 'trapezoid': Upper base (shorter/smaller), 'circle': Radius, 'ellipse': Shorter axis (similar to radius in circles)

areab.label: Value B
areab.tooltip: Each shape implies a value: 'rectangle': Height, 'triangle': Vertical height, 'parallelogram': Vertical height, 'trapezoid': Lower base (longer/larger), 'ellipse': Longer axis (similar to radius in circles)

areac.label: Value C
areac.tooltip: Each shape implies a value: 'trapezoid': Vertical height

erroredad.mensaje: You must select a birth date.

erroropera3.mensaje: The values for years, months, days, hours, minutes must be filled in. If no change applies, leave the value at 0.

errormatriculatipo.mensaje: A type of license plate must be selected.

domicilios.parrafo1: Generate a completely random address in CCAA, Province, Municipality, or select in the previous blocks a CCAA and province to generate them directed.
domicilios.parrafo2: Additionally, in this block, you can filter by the specific Municipality of a province to generate.

ccaa.label: CCAA Code
ccaa.tooltip: Auto-filled with the CCAA selected in the 'Provinces' block.

provincia.label: Province Code
provincia.tooltip: Auto-filled with the Province selected in the 'Municipalities' block.

municipio.label: Municipality Code
municipio.tooltip: This value should be filled if you want to filter addresses by municipality. The municipality code is related to the province, so it doesn't make sense on its own. You can copy it from one of the results in the 'Municipalities' block after filtering a province.

errorupcatamano.mensaje: The UPC-A code must be 11-12 numeric digits

errorupcetamano.mensaje: The UPC-E code must be 8 numeric digits

errorean13tamano.mensaje: The EAN-13 code must be 13 numeric digits

errorcode128tamano.mensaje: The Code-128 code must have a maximum of 80 characters

qr.parrafo1: QR codes are becoming the most recognized 2D barcodes worldwide. The great advantage of the QR code is that we can store large amounts of data in a limited space.
qr.parrafo2: They use four standardized encoding modes to store data efficiently.
qr.parrafo3: Additionally, they are flexible in size and can be easily scanned with a smartphone. Like PDF417, a QR code can withstand some damage without causing data loss.

147.parrafo1: PDF417 is a stacked linear barcode composed of multiple 1D barcodes stacked on top of each other. Therefore, it can use a traditional linear scanner.
147.parrafo2: We might expect to find it in a variety of applications, such as travel (boarding passes), ID cards, and inventory management.

ean13.parrafo1: EAN codes are known worldwide as European article numbers and international article numbers. They are designed to be read at the point of sale. There are also some different variations of the EAN code, such as EAN-13, EAN-8, JAN-13, and ISBN.
ean13.parrafo2: The EAN-13 code is the most widely used EAN standard. It consists of 13 digits: an initial '0' followed by the UPC-A code (12 digits).

code128.parrafo1: The Code 128 barcode is a compact, high-density linear code used in the logistics and transportation industries for orders and distribution.
code128.parrafo2: It can encode the 128 ASCII characters and its length is variable.

upca.parrafo1: UPC (Universal Product Code) codes are some of the most used 1D barcodes and are mainly found in the United States.
upca.parrafo2: The UPC-A is a numeric-only code that contains 12 digits: a manufacturer identification number (6 digits), an item number (5 digits), and a check digit.

upce.parrafo1: A variant of the UPC that has only 8 digits and is used for small packages.

ancho.label: Width
ancho.tooltip: Width of the image in pixels to generate. Leave blank to generate with the default value of the service.

alto.label: Height
alto.tooltip: Height of the image in pixels to generate. Leave blank to generate with the default value of the service.

valorcodificar.tooltip_128: Alphanumeric code of a maximum of 80 characters.
valorcodificar.tooltip_upca: 12-digit numeric code. You can omit the last one which is the check digit, and it will generate it below.

textoqrinf.label: Lower text

colorhexa.tooltip: Color in hexadecimal (starting with # or without it)

promopatron.label: Pattern
promopatron.tooltip: Optional. Pattern that generated codes will follow. The '-' is used as a separator of parts. The pattern will be indicated as 'AA-AAAAA-AAA-AAAA' and each part separated by the dash will be generated. If the pattern is filled, the length filled will be ignored.

promoprefijo.label: Prefix
promoprefijo.tooltip: Optional. Prefix to add in every promotional code in the form 'prefix-'.

promosufijo.label: Suffix
promosufijo.tooltip: Optional. Suffix to add in every promotional code in the form 'suffix-'.
